{
  "stem": "10862.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He had no conscience, so what-- he could have just as well have killed me too.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's a terrible fear.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's a fear that, that nags at you constantly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, January 17, 1945 things began to change.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had heard that the war was coming to an end, the Russians were coming closer and closer.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And actually started January 16th, 1945, and there was a lot of rumor going around in the camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A lot of whispering going around that the Germans, they're losing the war and that the Russians are coming in and we're going to be liberated and things like that.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But of January 16th of that evening, the Germans knew that the end was coming already.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Russians were pretty close to Czestochowa.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They decided to take the people out of the camps.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They came back at night.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They took everybody out, and some, they left in camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They called out all the people for an appel in the morning, all the women and men, and they called you by numbers.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now, when my number came up, my oldest sister Hannah walked out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "When they called Reva Mandelbaum, my sister walked out because she knew that if I would have gone out, I would have been killed that evening too.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were taking all the women and older men and they were putting them on trains.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They were going to take them all to Buchenwald, to another camp, because the Germans were seeing that they were losing, and they didn't want the Russians to find anybody in the camps.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were trying to clean out the camp.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that night they took my sister, Hannah, instead of me, my sister, Eda, and my brother all out into, to the box cars.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
